@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml
title Online Store architecture review thread
top to bottom direction
scale 759 width
skinparam nodesep 18
skinparam ranksep 24
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
rectangle "Trigger and scope\nDecision, boundary, version\nand review criteria" as S #FFF2CC
rectangle "Review package\nFocused views, ADRs, risks\nand test evidence" as P #DDEBF7
rectangle "Stakeholder questions\nFunctional, data, integration, security\nperformance, resilience, operability" as Q #DDEBF7
rectangle "Evidence assessment\nClaims, results, assumptions\nand gaps" as E #E2F0D9
rectangle "Governed findings\nRisk | decision | action | exception\nOwner and due or review date" as F #FCE4D6
rectangle "Review outcome" as O #E4DFEC
rectangle "Proceed" as A #E2F0D9
rectangle "Proceed with conditions" as C #FFF2CC
rectangle "Revise and return" as R #F4CCCC
rectangle "Owned follow-up\nCheck closure evidence\nand update records" as U #D9EAD3
S -right-> P : prepares
P -down-> Q : frames questions
Q -right-> E : tests with evidence
E -down-> F : records material findings
F --> O : informs decision
O -left-> A : sufficient evidence
O -down-> C : bounded conditions
O -right-> R : blocking gap or risk
A --> U : monitor commitments
C --> U : close conditions
R --> U : revise design or evidence
U .left.> P : focused feedback and re-review
legend bottom
Solid arrows show review and follow-up.
Dotted arrow shows iterative revision.
endlegend
@enduml
